\f1\b\fs32 \cf2 B. Mansion / Urban Mystery (16\'9630)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs28 \cf2 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	16.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Clockmaker\'92s Workshop (Temporal Gating)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Room cluttered with half-disassembled clocks. Central clock controls local time-of-day variable. Winding it advances time, changing NPC schedules and opening/closing other rooms (e.g., guards off shift at \'93night\'94). The player must set a specific time to reveal a secret hatch.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	17.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Portrait Gallery (Social / Perception)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Wall of family portraits, some eyes following the player. Examining reveals tiny mechanisms; moving portraits in the right sequence opens a panel. Sequence clue hidden in gossip: which relatives despised one another. Tests your framework\'92s ability to store NPC relationship hints and apply them to puzzles.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	18.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Locked Study with Listening Tube (Audio Clue)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Study door locked from inside. A brass listening tube leads under the door. Using it you hear an NPC muttering numbers or words that form a combination. If the player disturbs them elsewhere, they mutter a 
\f4\i different
\f3\i0  combination leading to an \'93incorrect but interesting\'94 outcome.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	19.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Greenhouse of Exotic Poison (Stealth / Mitigation)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Glasshouse full of toxic pollen. Entering unprotected slowly applies a \'93poisoned\'94 condition each turn. Clue: gardener\'92s notes about safe paths or protective masks. Pollen also affects enemies, so the player can kite them in. Good for lingering environmental hazards.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	20.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Ballroom with Ghostly Waltz (Pattern / Timing)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Empty ballroom where spectral dancers appear at intervals. Crossing the room requires moving in step with a ghostly waltz pattern (N, N, E, S, etc.). Missteps cause cold damage or teleportation back to entrance. The pattern may be hinted in music notation or an old dance manual.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	21.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Servant Passage Network (Secret Shortcuts)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Narrow, dusty corridors behind walls. Certain push-panels in other rooms open into this network. Within, player finds eavesdropping peepholes (view descriptions of other rooms), quick shortcuts, and hidden stashes. Good for stress-testing viewpoint and cross-room descriptions.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	22.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Kitchen of Infinite Leftovers (Looping Room)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Kitchen resets every time you leave and re-enter: pots move, NPC cook repeats a routine, leftovers regenerate. Exploit: take advantage of infinite food or repeated events to create stackable items (e.g., empty bottles) or to set up a \'93Groundhog Day\'94 style puzzle that needs multiple runs.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	23.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Household Shrine (Boon or Curse)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Small household altar. Offering different items yields randomized blessings or curses: temporary stat buffs, extra luck, or haunting. The shrine \'93remembers\'94 how respectful the player was earlier (e.g., if they vandalized religious objects, results skew negative).\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	24.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Stuffed Trophy Room (Mimic / Ambush)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Room filled with animal trophies. One mount is a living predator playing dead. If the player examines too closely or takes its teeth/trophy, it attacks. If they bring it something (raw meat, special scent), it becomes a secret ally or mount.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	25.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Sealed Panic Room (Constrained Escape)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Small metal-lined room, only one door, reinforced. Once the player enters and door locks, they must find a way out using limited in-room resources: ventilation duct, emergency codes scratched on wall, hidden mechanism behind painting. Great to test \'93single-room mini-escape\'94 logic.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	26.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Auction Hall (Social / Economics)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 NPCs bidding on items. Player can bid, bluff, or sabotage rivals. Items later serve as puzzle pieces elsewhere. Implement timed auction rounds, NPC bidding logic, and consequences if the player cheats or refuses to pay.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	27.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Nursery of Forgotten Toys (Emotion + Secret)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Child\'92s room with broken toys, tiny chairs. Interacting with toys triggers ghost-child responses: giggles, tantrums, or clues. Arranging three specific toys in a circle \'93starts a game\'94 that reveals a hidden compartment. Tests subtle, emotional feedback and multi-object configuration.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	28.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Tailor\'92s Fitting Room (Disguise Mechanics)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Mirrors, mannequins, racks of clothes. Player can assemble disguises by combining clothing pieces to pass as different factions or social classes. A guard at the next area checks for specific uniform features (badge, color). Good for testing composite gear and conditional access.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	29.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone City Rooftop Garden (Verticality / Risk)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Open rooftop with precarious edges. Player can attempt risky jumps to adjacent roofs, climb trellises, or drop into a skylight. Failed jumps cause injuries or landing in a lower, unwanted area. Wind or weather modifiers increase difficulty, giving your engine excuses for conditional text.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	30.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Printing Press Basement (Info Manipulation)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Underground printing press running off counterfeit pamphlets. Player can rewrite a leaflet to change public opinion, altering NPC crowd behavior in a later plaza scene. Needs persistent \'93city sentiment\'94 flags that unlock or block routes.\
