\f1\b\fs32 \cf2 D. Magical / Surreal (46\'9660)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\fs28 \cf2 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	46.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Library of Unwritten Books (Generative Clues)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Shelves full of blank books that fill with text describing the reader\'92s possible futures. Reading too much can create a \'93prophecy lock\'94 that restricts choices, but allows meta-hints. Destroying a book severs a future branch. Great for testing conditional text and future-prediction flavor.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	47.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Mirror Labyrinth (Self-Interaction)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Hall of mirrors that reflect slightly different versions of the PC. One reflection acts independently, mimicking earlier decisions. Player can trade items or info with own reflection, or trap an enemy reflection instead.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	48.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Colorless Garden (Color as Resource)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Garden drained of color. Player can \'93carry\'94 hues in a prism or paintbrush; applying color to objects animates them. Coloring a statue makes it talk; coloring a door sigil unlocks it. Track \'93color charges\'94 as a resource.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	49.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Gravity-Inverted Chamber (Movement Twists)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Entering flips gravity: ceiling becomes floor. Exits that were inaccessible now reachable. Items not anchored fall to previous \'93ceiling.\'94 Toggling gravity repeatedly rearranges the room state; some puzzles require stacking objects in both orientations.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f2\b \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone {\listtext	50.	}
\f0 \up0 \nosupersub \ulnone Dreaming Inn Room (Meta Save/Load)
\f3\b0 \uc0\u8232 Room at a magical inn. Sleeping here lets the player revisit earlier scenes in dream form, replaying events with limited interaction to change flags (e.g., plant an item retroactively). Your framework can treat these as special \'93flashback\'94 rooms that alter variables.\
\ls4\ilvl0
